Right. Requested in that at that time an African American wanted to study for some degree that was offered by one of the state's segregated colleges.

01:22:14.640 --> 01:22:26.640
Perhaps it might be offered out of state tuition. So I wrote to at that time Governor Strom Thurman and of course I never got a reply.

01:22:26.640 --> 01:22:36.640
I followed the procedures but never got a reply so I was kind of ignored altogether. Maybe the funds weren't available or I didn't have any political cloud or whatever but I wasn't able to do that.

01:22:36.640 --> 01:22:55.640
So the incident at state college in Klaaflan was what my fate was to be. But on Clemson that morning again things went along very quietly everything took place and again it became again the first of his race to go to Clemson.

01:22:55.640 --> 01:23:05.640
Incidentally back in the doing reconstruction African Americans had attended the University of South Carolina.

01:23:05.640 --> 01:23:14.640
